      "text": "@instablog9ja Temu’s price advantage is real, but the comparison isn’t apples-to-apples.\n\nJumia and Konga still win on local logistics and payment-on-delivery for a large share of Nigerian buyers. \n\nTemu wins on pure landed cost for non-urgent items. \n\nThe platforms that survive long-term will be the ones that close the gap on whichever side they’re currently weaker, not the ones that just claim the other is “dead.”",
